---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTABand from '@/components/CTABand.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Critical Illness Insurance | Heidi Blondin Financial"
  description="A tax-free lump sum if you're diagnosed with a serious illness. Learn how critical illness insurance works and who needs it — Heidi Blondin Financial, Kingston ON."
>

  <section class="bg-brand-plum py-20">
    <div class="container-content max-w-3xl">
      <p class="eyebrow-light mb-5">Insurance</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-display text-white text-balance" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">Critical Illness Insurance</h1>
      <p class="font-sans text-[18px] text-white/65 mt-5 leading-relaxed">
        A serious diagnosis changes everything. Critical illness insurance gives you a tax-free lump sum so you can focus on getting better — not on how you'll pay for it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white section-gap">
    <div class="container-content max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-brand-plum mb-6" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">What critical illness insurance covers</h2>
      <div class="font-sans text-[17px] text-brand-ink/75 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>Critical illness insurance pays a one-time, tax-free lump sum benefit if you're diagnosed with a covered serious illness and survive a waiting period (typically 30 days). Unlike disability insurance — which replaces your income on an ongoing basis — the CI benefit is paid all at once, giving you complete flexibility in how you use it.</p>
        <p>Most policies cover the three most common life-altering conditions: heart attack, stroke, and life-threatening cancer. Comprehensive policies may cover 25 or more conditions, including multiple sclerosis, Alzheimer's disease, organ failure, and more.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-brand-plum mb-5" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">What you can do with the benefit</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          {[
            'Cover out-of-pocket medical expenses not covered by OHIP',
            'Replace lost income while you\'re off work',
            'Pay for private care, home modifications, or specialized treatments',
            'Keep up with mortgage payments and household expenses',
            'Travel for treatment or convalescence',
            'Give yourself time to recover without rushing back to work',
          ].map(item => (
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3 bg-brand-tintSage p-4">
              <span class="text-brand-gold mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span class="font-sans text-[14px] text-brand-ink/70 leading-relaxed">{item}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-brand-plum mb-4" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">Is critical illness insurance right for you?</h2>
        <div class="font-sans text-[17px] text-brand-ink/75 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
          <p>Consider this: nearly 1 in 2 Canadians will develop cancer in their lifetime. Survival rates are improving — which means more people are living through serious illness and dealing with the financial consequences of it. If you're a working-age adult with financial obligations, CI insurance is worth serious consideration.</p>
          <p>It's particularly valuable if you are self-employed or your employer doesn't offer comprehensive disability benefits, if you have dependents who rely on your income, or if you want to preserve your savings and investments if you're ever unable to work for an extended period.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 bg-brand-tintPlum p-5 border-l-2 border-brand-plum/30">
        <p class="font-sans text-xs text-brand-ink/55 leading-relaxed">Insurance products are offered through Heidi Blondin Financial / Qualified Financial Services. This article is for general information purposes only and does not constitute personalized insurance advice. Coverage conditions and exclusions vary by policy and insurer. Please consult with a qualified advisor to determine what coverage is appropriate for your situation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABand heading="Get a critical illness quote" sub="Book a free consultation or request a quote and we'll find coverage that fits your situation and budget." />

</BaseLayout>
